<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-20T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="757" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6405: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-20T17:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            20, 1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February
                                    20—3:06 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>291. With regard to the signing of the armistice between Latvia and
                                the Bolsheviks reported to have been signed yesterday I learn
                                information at the Foreign Office that Finland and Lithuania are
                                expected to do likewise in the immediate future.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>